    {
      Id = "SaveErrorCorruptPC"
      DisplayName = "Corrupt Save Data"
      Description = """
      Something happened to your save data, and unfortunately it can no longer be read. Please follow these steps to attempt to restore it.

  		1. Navigate to {#AlertBoldFormat}/Saved Games/Hades II{#Prev}
  		2. Backup the entire folder
		  3. Sort by 'Date modified' to locate your most recent save matching one of these names (assuming you use Save Slot 1): {#AlertItalicFormat}Profile1_Temp.sav{#Prev}, {#AlertItalicFormat}Profile1_Temp.sav.bak{#Prev}, or {#AlertItalicFormat}Profile1.sav.bak{#Prev}
		  4. Rename that file to {#AlertItalicFormat}Profile1.sav{#Prev}
		  5. Then open the Play menu in-game and look for the save.

      If none of this helps, please see our Technical Support FAQ at: {#AlertBoldFormat}supergiant.games/hades2faq{#Prev}
		"""
    }
    {
      Id = "UnsupportedControllerPC"
      DisplayName = "Unrecognized Controller"
      Description = """
      We were unable to identify your game controller. Please try the following:

      · If using a wireless controller, a wired connection may fix this.

      · Enable Steam Input and relaunch Hades II. Or, disable Steam Input if it's enabled.

      · Try a different controller if you have one available.

      · If none of this helps, please see our Technical Support FAQ at: {#AlertBoldFormat}supergiant.games/hades2faq{#Prev}
    """
    }
    {
      Id = "UnsupportedControllerSteamInput"
      DisplayName = "Controller Notice"
      Description = """
      We detected that Steam Input is enabled, but we were unable to identify your game controller. If your controller functions normally in-game, you may safely disregard this message. Otherwise, we recommend the following:

      · Disable Steam Input and relaunch Hades II.

      · Configure your desired Button Labels under Options > Interface.

      · For a list of supported controllers, please see our Technical Support FAQ at: {#AlertBoldFormat}supergiant.games/hades2faq{#Prev}
    """
    }
