  	{
      Id = "SaveErrorPC"
      DisplayName = "Unable to Save"
      Description = """
      Your progress should have automatically saved just now, but something went wrong. Please try the following:

		  · If you are running antivirus software, try disabling it; or, whitelist {#AlertBoldFormat}Hades2.exe{#Prev}, and try running the game again

      · Ensure the game has write access to your save folder. Locate and right-click {#AlertBoldFormat}%USERPROFILE%/Saved Games/Hades II{#Prev}, select {#AlertItalicFormat}Properties{#Prev}, and ensure {#AlertItalicFormat}Read-only {#Prev}is {#AlertItalicFormat}not {#Prev}selected; on the Security tab, ensure your account has {#AlertItalicFormat}Full control {#Prev}or {#AlertItalicFormat}Modify {#Prev}permissions

      · Locate {#AlertBoldFormat}Hades2.exe {#Prev}in your install folder, and run it with {#AlertBoldFormat}Administrator {#Prev}privileges {#AlertItalicFormat}(in the right-click menu){#Prev}

      · If none of this helps, please see our Technical Support FAQ at: {#AlertBoldFormat}supergiant.games/hades2faq{#Prev}
      """
    }
    {
      Id = "FileAccessErrorPC"
      DisplayName = "Unable to Read Data"
      Description = """
			Something went wrong, and the game was unable to read or access files needed for it to run properly. Please try the following:

			· If you are running antivirus software, try disabling it; or, whitelist {#AlertBoldFormat}Hades2.exe{#Prev}, and try running the game again

      · Ensure the game has write access to your save data folder:
            {#AlertBoldFormat}%USERPROFILE%/Saved Games/Hades II{#Prev}
            {#AlertItalicFormat}(Right-click it, select {#Prev}Properties{#AlertItalicFormat}, and ensure {#Prev}Read-only {#AlertItalicFormat}is NOT selected){#Prev}

			· Locate {#AlertBoldFormat}Hades2.exe {#Prev}in your install folder, and run it with {#AlertBoldFormat}Administrator {#Prev}privileges {#AlertItalicFormat}(in the right-click menu){#Prev}

      · If none of this helps, please see our Technical Support FAQ at: {#AlertBoldFormat}supergiant.games/hades2faq{#Prev}
      """
    }
	{
      Id = "DataFileCorrupt"
      DisplayName = "Unable to Read Data"
      Description = """
			Something went wrong, and the game was unable to read or access files needed for it to run properly. Please try the following:

			· Verify the integrity of the game files through the launcher

			· If you are running antivirus software, try disabling it; or, whitelist {#AlertBoldFormat}Hades2.exe{#Prev}, and try running the game again

      · Re-install the game entirely

      · If none of this helps, please see our Technical Support FAQ at: {#AlertBoldFormat}supergiant.games/hades2faq{#Prev}
      """
    }

