    }
    {
      Id = "CloudSaves_Help"
      DisplayName = "Cross-Saves"
      Description = """
      If you play {#AlertHeaderFormat}Hades II {#Prev}on a personal computer as well as {#AlertHighlightFormat}Nintendo Switch{#Prev}, you can transfer your save data using {#AlertHighlightFormat}Cross-Saves{#Prev}!

      {!Icons.DivLong}

      {#AlertBoldFormat}Getting Started: {#Prev}To enable {#AlertHighlightFormat}Cross-Saves{#Prev}, on the previous screen, connect to either {#AlertHighlightFormat}Steam {#Prev}or {#AlertHighlightFormat}Epic Games {#Prev} by signing in to your secure account.

      Once enabled, your save data on your {#AlertHighlightFormat}Nintendo Switch {#Prev}will sync with your cloud save data on {#AlertHighlightFormat}Steam {#Prev}or {#AlertHighlightFormat}Epic Games {#Prev}whenever you bring up the {#AlertHighlightFormat}Play Menu {#Prev}{#AlertItalicFormat}(to choose a save slot to load){#Prev}.

      {#AlertBoldFormat}Uploading Save Data: {#Prev}After a play session, pause the game and select {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sync & Quit {#Prev}to automatically upload your progress.

      Assuming you have cloud saves enabled on {#AlertHighlightFormat}Steam {#Prev}or {#AlertHighlightFormat}Epic Games{#Prev}, you can then continue on your computer where you left off!

      {#AlertBoldFormat}Troubleshooting: {#Prev}You need a live Internet connection to sync {#AlertHighlightFormat}Cross-Saves{#Prev}. In some cases, a save conflict may occur between versions. You may then choose whether to use local save data or cloud save data.

      If you have a different game going in the same save slot on both your computer and {#AlertHighlightFormat}Nintendo Switch{#Prev}, to prevent a save conflict, please rename your computer save data to reference a different save slot.

      For example, if you use the first save slot, search for {#AlertBoldFormat}Profile1.sav {#Prev}on your computer, and rename it to {#AlertBoldFormat}Profile2.sav{#Prev}. {#AlertHighlightFormat}Cross-Saves {#Prev}should then sync so that you have your two separate games in two separate save slots.
     
      Thank you for playing, and good luck killing Time!
      """
    }
    {
      Id = "CloudSaves_Help_Alt"
      DisplayName = "Cross-Saves"
      Description = """
      If you play {#AlertHeaderFormat}Hades II {#Prev}on a personal computer as well as {#AlertHighlightFormat}Nintendo Switch 2{#Prev}, you can transfer your save data using {#AlertHighlightFormat}Cross-Saves{#Prev}!

      {!Icons.DivLong}

      {#AlertBoldFormat}Getting Started: {#Prev}To enable {#AlertHighlightFormat}Cross-Saves{#Prev}, on the previous screen, connect to either {#AlertHighlightFormat}Steam {#Prev}or {#AlertHighlightFormat}Epic Games {#Prev} by signing in to your secure account.

      Once enabled, your save data on your {#AlertHighlightFormat}Nintendo Switch 2 {#Prev}will sync with your cloud save data on {#AlertHighlightFormat}Steam {#Prev}or {#AlertHighlightFormat}Epic Games {#Prev}whenever you bring up the {#AlertHighlightFormat}Play Menu {#Prev}{#AlertItalicFormat}(to choose a save slot to load){#Prev}.

      {#AlertBoldFormat}Uploading Save Data: {#Prev}After a play session, pause the game and select {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sync & Quit {#Prev}to automatically upload your progress.

      Assuming you have cloud saves enabled on {#AlertHighlightFormat}Steam {#Prev}or {#AlertHighlightFormat}Epic Games{#Prev}, you can then continue on your computer where you left off!

      {#AlertBoldFormat}Troubleshooting: {#Prev}You need a live Internet connection to sync {#AlertHighlightFormat}Cross-Saves{#Prev}. In some cases, a save conflict may occur between versions. You may then choose whether to use local save data or cloud save data.

      If you have a different game going in the same save slot on both your computer and {#AlertHighlightFormat}Nintendo Switch 2{#Prev}, to prevent a save conflict, please rename your computer save data to reference a different save slot.

      For example, if you use the first save slot, search for {#AlertBoldFormat}Profile1.sav {#Prev}on your computer, and rename it to {#AlertBoldFormat}Profile2.sav{#Prev}. {#AlertHighlightFormat}Cross-Saves {#Prev}should then sync so that you have your two separate games in two separate save slots.
     
      Thank you for playing, and good luck killing Time!
      """
    }
